Hear the four achievements of the new version of the national anthem. 
On Sunday, on the occasion of the Day of the Czech nationality, Prime Minister Mirek Topolánek solemnly presented the new recordings of the national anthem Kde domov můj (Where is my homeland?). 
The anthem has been recorded by the orchestra of the National Theater under the direction of Jiří Bělohlávek. 
We have four versions - with a female or male solo song, an interpretation with chorus and an instrumental version. 
The song is provided by Kateřina Kněžínková and Adam Plachetka. 
Otakar Jeremiáš and Jaroslav Krček are the authors of the arrangements of the anthem. 
You can listen to the four new versions on the iHNed.cz. server 
Bělohlávek considers the Czech national song as one of the most beautiful hymns. 
As he had already given to the Český rozhlas (the Czech public radio), he has chosen for the interpretation of the solo versions of singers with voices young and representative, who are marked and appreciated. 
"Since the beginning, I was trying to take care that the two singers, as well as the chorus, have a good diction, so that we understand the words they sing of simultaneous way," he said. 
The Czech national anthem, next year, will celebrate its 175è anniversary. 
The song Kde domov můj rings for the first time in 1834 on the boards of Stavovské divadlo (the theatre of states) in Fidlovačka (Kermesse), original cobblers of Czech Josef Kajetán Tyl, accompanied by the music of František Škroup. 
It has become popular and people have spontaneously appropriate. 
After the creation of the Tchécoslaovaquie in 1918, the first song, of course, became an integral part of the national anthem. 
It remained one of the seven national symbols, even after the creation of the independent Czech Republic. 
